gomodel:SYNGO_1627  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Quantitative mass spectrometric analyses (iBAQ) of purified synaptosomes indicate the presence of ARHGDIA in synaptic terminals.\n\n10/10/2017 Pim\n- Listed as rho GDI 1 in Table S2\n\n15/10/2017 Frank\n- should be \"rho GDI 1\" from Table S2, which is \"ARHGDIA, Rattus norvegicus, Swiss-Prot, Rho GDP-dissociation inhibitor 1 (Rho GDI 1) (Rho-GDI alpha)\". Experimental description: From main text \"To quantify the organization of synaptic vesicle recycling, we first purified synaptic boutons (synaptosomes) from the cellular layers of the cortex and cerebellum of adult rats, using a modified version of a classical brain fractionation protocol." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1627" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

